WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:28.600 --> 00:00:32.600
-Can't I come to Paris?
-I was waiting...

3
00:00:32.400 --> 00:00:35.200
I'm left at home
alone like a little kid

4
00:00:35.100 --> 00:00:39.500
And me at Ravoux's
staring at a great wall?

5
00:00:39.300 --> 00:00:41.900
So why live there?

6
00:00:41.800 --> 00:00:59.600
&nbsp

7
00:00:58.900 --> 00:01:00.500
"Week" takes two e's

8
00:01:00.400 --> 00:01:05.400
There's also "w-e-a-k"...
That's what I am with you two

9
00:01:05.200 --> 00:01:07.600
This is "w-e-e-k"

10
00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:07.700
&nbsp

11
00:01:07.700 --> 00:01:09.400
What's got into him?

12
00:01:09.300 --> 00:01:14.300
Think he doesn't know? You were
gone all day. It's not done!

13
00:01:14.100 --> 00:01:16.800
Look at you!

14
00:01:16.700 --> 00:01:47.000
&nbsp

15
00:01:45.800 --> 00:01:47.100
You'll get pregnant

16
00:01:47.000 --> 00:01:47.200
&nbsp

17
00:01:47.200 --> 00:01:48.800
How would you know?

18
00:01:48.800 --> 00:01:50.300
I had a baby boy at your age

19
00:01:50.200 --> 00:01:53.900
Really?
You never told us

20
00:01:53.800 --> 00:01:54.100
&nbsp

21
00:01:54.000 --> 00:02:00.600
He joined the Commune in 1870
We never saw him again

22
00:02:00.400 --> 00:02:01.400
&nbsp

23
00:02:01.300 --> 00:02:03.500
When it was over..

24
00:02:03.400 --> 00:02:06.900
..the army moved into Paris

25
00:02:06.800 --> 00:02:07.200
&nbsp

26
00:02:07.200 --> 00:02:11.200
He didn't come home

27
00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:14.400
They summoned me

28
00:02:14.300 --> 00:02:17.100
I was his body laid out
with the others.

29
00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:17.900
&nbsp

30
00:02:17.800 --> 00:02:20.000
He was 15

31
00:02:19.900 --> 00:02:27.300
&nbsp

32
00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:29.000
Poor you

33
00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:30.300
&nbsp

34
00:02:30.200 --> 00:02:31.700
That's all past

35
00:02:31.600 --> 00:02:34.400
No. nothing's ever past

36
00:02:34.300 --> 00:02:35.300
&nbsp

37
00:02:35.300 --> 00:02:37.500
It's past...

38
00:02:37.400 --> 00:02:41.700
But Van Gogh may
not be a reliable man

39
00:02:41.500 --> 00:03:33.300
&nbsp

40
00:03:31.200 --> 00:03:33.600
I was behind you. Where'd you
go?

41
00:03:33.500 --> 00:03:35.500
I had me a drink

42
00:03:35.500 --> 00:03:36.900
&nbsp

43
00:03:36.800 --> 00:03:39.500
King size. Overdoing it again!

44
00:03:39.400 --> 00:03:40.500
&nbsp

45
00:03:40.400 --> 00:03:42.900
Damn fairy!

46
00:03:42.800 --> 00:04:03.300
&nbsp

47
00:04:02.500 --> 00:04:04.100
You could help me

48
00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:04.300
&nbsp

49
00:04:04.300 --> 00:04:05.200
Your folks out?

50
00:04:05.200 --> 00:04:07.300
Dunno where they are

51
00:04:07.200 --> 00:04:25.400
&nbsp

52
00:04:24.700 --> 00:04:26.100
It's paid

53
00:04:26.000 --> 00:04:28.500
I owed you for one

54
00:04:28.400 --> 00:04:32.600
&nbsp

55
00:04:32.400 --> 00:04:35.500
Go right ahead!
Want my wife too?

56
00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:35.500
&nbsp

57
00:04:35.500 --> 00:04:39.600
No. Your daughter maybe. But
she helps herself. like us

58
00:04:39.400 --> 00:04:42.400
-You're some guard keeper!
-What?

59
00:04:42.300 --> 00:04:45.000
The train nearly ran
a man over

60
00:04:44.900 --> 00:04:49.900
Ran a man over? In 20 years I
never saw it happen

61
00:04:49.700 --> 00:04:59.200
&nbsp

62
00:04:58.800 --> 00:05:01.600
Hello. maestro

63
00:05:01.500 --> 00:05:04.800
&nbsp

64
00:05:04.700 --> 00:05:06.800
Could I?

65
00:05:06.700 --> 00:05:07.100
&nbsp

66
00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:10.200
I wanted a peek...
if you don't mind

67
00:05:10.100 --> 00:05:12.200
It's in the back

68
00:05:12.100 --> 00:05:14.200
&nbsp

69
00:05:14.100 --> 00:05:16.300
One more. and I'll be there

70
00:05:16.200 --> 00:05:41.200
&nbsp

71
00:05:40.200 --> 00:05:42.300
What changes since you left
Paris!

72
00:05:42.200 --> 00:05:48.000
Such a daring approach to
pointillism! It's exquisite

73
00:05:47.800 --> 00:05:49.000
&nbsp

74
00:05:48.900 --> 00:05:51.500
My paintings are there

75
00:05:51.400 --> 00:05:54.800
&nbsp

76
00:05:54.700 --> 00:05:58.400
I'm relieved
I was being hypocritical

77
00:05:58.200 --> 00:05:58.700
&nbsp

78
00:05:58.700 --> 00:06:01.700
As if I told you that thing...

79
00:06:01.600 --> 00:06:04.900
...was the future of art

80
00:06:04.700 --> 00:06:10.500
&nbsp

81
00:06:10.300 --> 00:06:13.100
But with that..

82
00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:16.100
I can be sincere

83
00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:19.300
If I could do that

84
00:06:19.100 --> 00:06:24.600
&nbsp

85
00:06:24.400 --> 00:06:26.300
Look!

86
00:06:26.200 --> 00:06:26.600
&nbsp

87
00:06:26.600 --> 00:06:28.900
Your St. Remy self-portrait

88
00:06:28.800 --> 00:06:34.800
&nbsp

89
00:06:34.600 --> 00:06:38.800
You often finish
paintings in the studio?

90
00:06:38.600 --> 00:06:38.800
&nbsp

91
00:06:38.800 --> 00:06:41.900
Happens...Bits and pieces..

92
00:06:41.800 --> 00:06:42.000
&nbsp

93
00:06:42.000 --> 00:06:44.500
That's my garden and
Marguerite...

94
00:06:44.400 --> 00:06:47.800
&nbsp

95
00:06:47.600 --> 00:06:51.100
Coco's favorite acacia...

96
00:06:51.000 --> 00:06:58.900
&nbsp

97
00:06:58.600 --> 00:07:01.100
That's good too

98
00:07:01.000 --> 00:07:07.700
&nbsp

99
00:07:07.400 --> 00:07:11.200
Hello. Are you better?

100
00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:12.900
The oozing stopped?

101
00:07:12.900 --> 00:07:14.800
&nbsp

102
00:07:14.700 --> 00:07:16.900
Two portraits of me!
I'm honored

103
00:07:16.800 --> 00:07:18.400
I always do a copy

104
00:07:18.300 --> 00:07:19.900
Which do I prefer?

105
00:07:19.900 --> 00:07:22.400
You'll only get one.

106
00:07:22.300 --> 00:07:22.800
&nbsp

107
00:07:22.800 --> 00:07:24.200
What a treat!

108
00:07:24.100 --> 00:07:26.100
My models always get the copy

109
00:07:26.000 --> 00:07:27.800
Really?

110
00:07:27.700 --> 00:07:29.300
&nbsp

111
00:07:29.300 --> 00:07:32.300
Teach me your cut-reed
technique

112
00:07:32.200 --> 00:07:35.100
It's ismple
you just cut a reed

113
00:07:34.900 --> 00:07:40.600
Theo doesn't push your work
Dear Theo is being retentive

114
00:07:40.400 --> 00:07:43.300
I know

115
00:07:43.200 --> 00:07:47.300
You laugh. but it shatters me
I told him to see you

116
00:07:47.100 --> 00:07:49.700
Is he ill?

117
00:07:49.600 --> 00:07:50.100
&nbsp

118
00:07:50.100 --> 00:07:55.700
I meant your career. It's coming
along. Aurier's piece was fine

119
00:07:55.500 --> 00:07:56.800
He's an idiot

120
00:07:56.700 --> 00:08:02.300
Very literary. Writers don't 
understand painting

121
00:08:02.100 --> 00:08:02.500
&nbsp

122
00:08:02.500 --> 00:08:05.600
My daughter said you were
worried...

123
00:08:05.400 --> 00:08:07.500
That stinging pain?

124
00:08:07.500 --> 00:08:11.200
Please. I'm her father

125
00:08:11.000 --> 00:08:12.900
I'm here to help you

126
00:08:12.800 --> 00:08:13.000
&nbsp

127
00:08:13.000 --> 00:08:14.800
No. to cure me

128
00:08:14.800 --> 00:08:18.500
You're in fine health.
but a hypochondriac

129
00:08:18.300 --> 00:08:21.700
At St. Remy you thrived
on your illness

130
00:08:21.600 --> 00:08:25.300
I'm no expert
But my fits weren't imaginary

131
00:08:25.100 --> 00:08:29.700
You doctors aren't patients
When you are. then what?

132
00:08:29.500 --> 00:08:34.100
We cease to be doctors
You should be on a diet

133
00:08:33.900 --> 00:08:34.800
I'll wrap it up

134
00:08:34.800 --> 00:08:39.200
I'll parade with your masterpiece
You're muscular. like me

135
00:08:39.000 --> 00:08:42.300
Exercise! I don't laze in my
studio

136
00:08:42.200 --> 00:08:44.400
My legs go in my art. too

137
00:08:44.300 --> 00:08:49.000
Your painting hasn't found
its price. only its pace!

138
00:08:48.800 --> 00:09:00.400
&nbsp

139
00:08:59.900 --> 00:09:04.400
What the hell are you doing?

140
00:09:04.300 --> 00:09:08.200
That pink haze there
upsets the balance

141
00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:10.100
I'm removing it

142
00:09:10.000 --> 00:09:11.000
&nbsp

143
00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:13.400
It's a big mistake

144
00:09:13.300 --> 00:09:17.000
That's much better

145
00:09:16.800 --> 00:09:20.900
&nbsp

146
00:09:20.800 --> 00:09:24.300
I like fluid
airy things like Turner

147
00:09:24.100 --> 00:09:24.300
&nbsp

148
00:09:24.300 --> 00:09:27.700
I soar
above this earthbound art

149
00:09:27.600 --> 00:09:28.900
Earthbound

150
00:09:28.800 --> 00:09:31.800
Those mechanical strokes

151
00:09:31.700 --> 00:09:32.400
&nbsp

152
00:09:32.400 --> 00:09:36.500
Your paintings are too big!

153
00:09:36.300 --> 00:09:37.300
&nbsp

154
00:09:37.300 --> 00:09:39.400
Too big?

155
00:09:39.300 --> 00:09:43.800
How come you copied them 5
times?

156
00:09:43.600 --> 00:09:46.500
&nbsp

157
00:09:46.400 --> 00:09:50.900
Mine are ecstasy...fluidity...

158
00:09:50.700 --> 00:09:50.800
&nbsp

159
00:09:50.800 --> 00:09:53.800
Look what you do?
It's so thick...

160
00:09:53.700 --> 00:09:58.500
...the leaves are like the water
or the sky. It's all the same

161
00:09:58.300 --> 00:10:02.800
There's no glaze
You don't know how to glaze

162
00:10:02.600 --> 00:10:07.300
All those layers
all those strokes

163
00:10:07.100 --> 00:10:09.900
It's all bunched up

164
00:10:09.800 --> 00:10:10.300
&nbsp

165
00:10:10.300 --> 00:10:11.900
There's no feeling...

166
00:10:11.800 --> 00:10:13.400
You through?

167
00:10:13.300 --> 00:10:14.500
Look at that...

168
00:10:14.500 --> 00:10:16.500
You through?

169
00:10:16.400 --> 00:10:30.200
&nbsp

170
00:10:29.700 --> 00:10:32.300
I saw his paintings..Superb!

171
00:10:32.100 --> 00:10:34.300
I'm proud. he's like family

172
00:10:34.300 --> 00:10:36.300
He always will be

173
00:10:36.200 --> 00:10:41.700
We have 6 rooms and you won't take
him in. His room isn't a room

174
00:10:41.500 --> 00:10:44.500
-You've seen it?
-No. but I can imagine

175
00:10:44.300 --> 00:10:47.600
You'd like him
sleeping nearer to you

176
00:10:47.500 --> 00:10:50.200
The insane can be
dangerous company

177
00:10:50.100 --> 00:10:51.800
What do you mean?

178
00:10:51.700 --> 00:10:53.800
I mean in general

179
00:10:53.700 --> 00:10:57.400
You said he's normal. in good
health. Make up your mind!

180
00:10:57.300 --> 00:11:03.100
He cut his own ear. The fits
at the asylum in St. Remy...

181
00:11:02.900 --> 00:11:08.300
Lock me up and I'd have fits too.
His brother never visited him

182
00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:13.000
His real trouble is the
syphilis he's had for years

183
00:11:12.800 --> 00:11:17.000
Mom had it too. She died of it.
You have it to her

184
00:11:16.900 --> 00:11:20.600
Don't talk like that!
Not in that tone!

185
00:11:20.400 --> 00:11:22.800
His influence again!

186
00:11:22.700 --> 00:11:24.600
&nbsp

187
00:11:24.500 --> 00:11:28.200
They said she'd go blind
she was put in a dark room

188
00:11:28.100 --> 00:11:33.100
Aunt Francia told me
I was sent away to Lille

189
00:11:32.900 --> 00:11:37.500
Your mother was always in
poor health. What is this?

190
00:11:37.300 --> 00:11:42.100
I read bits of your medical
books. You hid things from us

191
00:11:41.900 --> 00:11:47.500
I was young. kids notice things.
Unhappiness affects them

192
00:11:47.300 --> 00:11:48.500
&nbsp

193
00:11:48.400 --> 00:11:53.200
What's got into you? You're
hysterical. like your mother

194
00:11:53.000 --> 00:11:58.500
To you Vincent's hysterical
we all are. It's fashionable

195
00:11:58.300 --> 00:12:03.800
You aspire toliberal thinking
but you wind up a bigot

196
00:12:03.600 --> 00:12:07.400
You can't cure him. You do
nothing! He came to be cured!

197
00:12:07.200 --> 00:12:11.100
It's as wrong to say he's mad.
as to say he's not

198
00:12:11.000 --> 00:12:12.500
I'm in love with him!

199
00:12:12.400 --> 00:12:15.000
-What?
-I'm in love with him!

200
00:12:14.900 --> 00:12:15.500
&nbsp

201
00:12:15.500 --> 00:12:16.900
You'd marry that...

202
00:12:16.800 --> 00:12:19.100
Who said marriage?

203
00:12:19.000 --> 00:12:20.300
&nbsp

204
00:12:20.300 --> 00:12:22.000
You'd live with a madman...

205
00:12:21.900 --> 00:12:25.500
No madder than you. He loves
me. wants to live with me

206
00:12:25.400 --> 00:12:27.400
-He told you?
-No. but I know it

207
00:12:27.300 --> 00:12:32.300
So much for your liberalism!
You apply it to others. but not me

208
00:12:32.100 --> 00:12:35.000
You're like everyone else

209
00:12:34.900 --> 00:12:35.900
&nbsp

210
00:12:35.800 --> 00:12:37.600
I have no set ideas. but
this...

211
00:12:37.600 --> 00:12:42.300
In theory. you're considerate.
modern...free love and all that...

212
00:12:42.100 --> 00:12:46.100
But in practice. forget it.
You're a coward

213
00:12:45.900 --> 00:12:48.500
That's why you can't paint!

214
00:12:48.400 --> 00:12:49.100
&nbsp

215
00:12:49.100 --> 00:12:52.600
What you just said is
unforgivable

216
00:12:52.400 --> 00:13:00.100
&nbsp

217
00:12:59.800 --> 00:13:02.700
Good news. I convinced Theo

218
00:13:02.600 --> 00:13:07.100
Jo and the baby will spend
the summer here

219
00:13:06.900 --> 00:13:07.100
&nbsp

220
00:13:07.100 --> 00:13:10.800
Glad?

221
00:13:10.700 --> 00:13:23.500
&nbsp

222
00:13:22.900 --> 00:13:27.200
It's unfair to slave and earn
no money from one's work

223
00:13:27.100 --> 00:13:30.100
You earn something
from your work

224
00:13:29.900 --> 00:13:30.000
&nbsp

225
00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:33.100
You're going to support me?

226
00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:36.100
I know Theo won't help 
me any more

227
00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:41.000
Some days painting revolts me
Maybe it's just as well

228
00:13:40.800 --> 00:13:46.900
I write Theo that all's find
He doesn't realize what I'm doing

229
00:13:46.600 --> 00:13:46.900
&nbsp

230
00:13:46.900 --> 00:13:52.300
Maybe he does. What can he tell?
That it's no good? He can't

231
00:13:52.100 --> 00:13:55.000
-You always defend him!
-I try to understand

232
00:13:54.900 --> 00:13:57.900
I know what's up

233
00:13:57.800 --> 00:14:02.300
Don't talk about
things you don't know

234
00:14:02.100 --> 00:14:05.900
The Van Goghs aren't
an artistic family

235
00:14:05.700 --> 00:14:08.200
The way my father looked
at me

236
00:14:08.100 --> 00:14:11.800
My work had to be really
ugly and dirty to him

237
00:14:11.700 --> 00:14:14.800
for me to get that look

238
00:14:14.600 --> 00:14:20.400
I just went on painting
in my own way. That's all

239
00:14:20.200 --> 00:14:22.500
&nbsp

240
00:14:22.400 --> 00:14:24.700
I Keep at it..

241
00:14:24.600 --> 00:14:24.800
&nbsp

242
00:14:24.800 --> 00:14:27.400
But what's the use

243
00:14:27.300 --> 00:14:28.100
&nbsp

244
00:14:28.100 --> 00:14:31.400
True. things are chaning.
You help me more than Kate...

245
00:14:31.200 --> 00:14:32.400
Thanks alot!

246
00:14:32.400 --> 00:14:34.600
Maybe if I'd met you instead
of her...

247
00:14:34.500 --> 00:14:37.600
You're lucky she didn't work out
People say...

248
00:14:37.500 --> 00:14:41.800
...her rejection of you
drove you to paint great art

249
00:14:41.600 --> 00:14:46.200
I say. with a decent girl you'd
have done even better work

250
00:14:46.000 --> 00:14:47.800
If that's what you think

251
00:14:47.700 --> 00:14:49.500
Yes. I do

252
00:14:49.500 --> 00:14:51.400
&nbsp

253
00:14:51.300 --> 00:14:55.200
Stop complaining! you're gifted!
Forget your brother and his wife

254
00:14:55.000 --> 00:14:55.500
&nbsp

255
00:14:55.500 --> 00:14:58.000
Forget all that

256
00:14:57.900 --> 00:15:01.200
Only you can make
the name Van Gogh famous!

257
00:15:01.100 --> 00:15:02.700
Are we married?

258
00:15:02.600 --> 00:15:03.300
&nbsp

259
00:15:03.300 --> 00:15:05.400
You sound like my wife

260
00:15:05.300 --> 00:15:09.500
Look. they're not pushing you
you're towing them all

261
00:15:09.300 --> 00:15:12.100
They're jealous of
what you've got

262
00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:14.500
Nothing was good
enough for your Kate

263
00:15:14.400 --> 00:15:20.300
Those women always marry
the idiots they deserve!

264
00:15:20.100 --> 00:15:21.300
&nbsp

265
00:15:21.200 --> 00:15:25.100
And you're moping over her

266
00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:25.600
&nbsp

267
00:15:25.600 --> 00:15:28.400
Why are you going to Paris
Sunday?

268
00:15:28.200 --> 00:15:31.400
-To get sloshed
-You can't do that here?

269
00:15:31.300 --> 00:15:34.000
To get sloshed!

270
00:15:33.900 --> 00:15:34.700
&nbsp

271
00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:36.100
Notice anything?

272
00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:38.400
I konow them by heart

273
00:15:38.300 --> 00:15:42.500
&nbsp

274
00:15:42.300 --> 00:15:46.400
We're out of the woods. Theo
will soon smother you with jewels

275
00:15:46.300 --> 00:15:48.700
I'll sell for less

276
00:15:48.600 --> 00:15:49.700
&nbsp

277
00:15:49.600 --> 00:15:51.700
There's only 30
And the rest?

278
00:15:51.600 --> 00:15:54.100
At Tanguy's

279
00:15:54.000 --> 00:15:54.300
&nbsp

280
00:15:54.300 --> 00:15:56.600
I'll go to Clauzel Street

281
00:15:56.500 --> 00:16:01.900
Watch out if you run into
people. You scare everyone

282
00:16:01.700 --> 00:16:08.400
&nbsp

283
00:16:08.200 --> 00:16:10.900
He picks fights in Paris

284
00:16:10.700 --> 00:16:10.900
&nbsp

285
00:16:10.900 --> 00:16:13.700
He's a grown man

286
00:16:13.600 --> 00:16:15.000
&nbsp

287
00:16:15.000 --> 00:16:17.900
He's eccentric...But like
anyone else..

288
00:16:17.700 --> 00:16:20.800
...he need help..

289
00:16:20.700 --> 00:16:26.500
We can't do anything
except relieve our own guilt

290
00:16:26.300 --> 00:16:28.700
&nbsp

291
00:16:28.600 --> 00:16:32.500
Like charity. that makes the
donors feel good

292
00:16:32.300 --> 00:16:37.300
&nbsp

293
00:16:37.100 --> 00:16:39.900
Those 50 franc bills...

294
00:16:39.800 --> 00:16:42.200
They relieve you more
than him

295
00:16:42.100 --> 00:16:42.700
&nbsp

296
00:16:42.700 --> 00:16:44.500
Am I right?

297
00:16:44.400 --> 00:16:47.200
&nbsp

298
00:16:47.100 --> 00:16:48.800
-Get rid of this for me
-What?

299
00:16:48.700 --> 00:16:50.500
-There
-I hate that..

300
00:16:50.500 --> 00:16:54.000
Go on. squeeze

301
00:16:53.800 --> 00:16:55.200
That's it

302
00:16:55.200 --> 00:17:08.100
&nbsp

303
00:17:07.500 --> 00:17:10.900
He should've been one of the
best painters of his time

304
00:17:10.800 --> 00:17:11.400
&nbsp

305
00:17:11.400 --> 00:17:15.200
But he started late and
rushed things

306
00:17:15.000 --> 00:17:16.700
He always does

307
00:17:16.700 --> 00:17:17.000
&nbsp

308
00:17:16.900 --> 00:17:20.400
like when he wanted to be a
priest

309
00:17:20.300 --> 00:17:20.900
&nbsp

310
00:17:20.900 --> 00:17:23.000
He never learned

311
00:17:22.900 --> 00:17:26.900
&nbsp
I don't understand him

312
00:17:26.700 --> 00:17:30.800
The truth is

313
00:17:30.700 --> 00:17:34.100
...deep down I don't like his
painting

314
00:17:33.900 --> 00:17:35.200
&nbsp

315
00:17:35.200 --> 00:17:37.800
I wish he painted like Renoir

316
00:17:37.700 --> 00:17:38.500
&nbsp

317
00:17:38.400 --> 00:17:41.200
I'd love that

318
00:17:41.100 --> 00:17:41.700
&nbsp

319
00:17:41.700 --> 00:17:46.200
No. I don't want him
to paint like Renoir

320
00:17:46.000 --> 00:17:50.800
&nbsp

321
00:17:50.600 --> 00:17:54.800
Not that. either. But if
Renoir painted like Vincent

322
00:17:54.700 --> 00:17:55.500
&nbsp

323
00:17:55.400 --> 00:17:59.600
I'd like it because my
brother hadn't done it. See?

324
00:17:59.500 --> 00:18:01.900
What nonsense

325
00:18:01.800 --> 00:18:04.600
You complicate everything

326
00:18:04.400 --> 00:18:08.300
Life just happens. that's all

327
00:18:08.200 --> 00:18:10.000
&nbsp

328
00:18:09.900 --> 00:18:12.600
Shall I rinse you down?

329
00:18:12.500 --> 00:18:47.100
&nbsp

330
00:18:45.700 --> 00:18:48.800
Vollard's wrong to play
the crafty dealer

331
00:18:48.700 --> 00:18:51.300
Clever people act dumb

332
00:18:51.200 --> 00:18:55.800
No. people prefer
to deal with the craftiest

333
00:18:55.600 --> 00:18:57.300
Come here...

334
00:18:57.200 --> 00:19:00.300
Look at these marvels

335
00:19:00.200 --> 00:19:02.300
Very nice

336
00:19:02.200 --> 00:19:04.300
Beautiful

337
00:19:04.200 --> 00:19:35.000
&nbsp

338
00:19:33.800 --> 00:19:37.600
That painting grows on me

339
00:19:37.400 --> 00:19:40.500
All those shades of blue

340
00:19:40.400 --> 00:19:44.500
As perfect as a Tiepolo

341
00:19:44.300 --> 00:19:45.500
&nbsp

342
00:19:45.500 --> 00:19:49.600
He painted it when
the baby was born

343
00:19:49.400 --> 00:19:49.600
&nbsp

344
00:19:49.600 --> 00:19:52.800
It's there so I can see it
from my bed when I wake up

345
00:19:52.700 --> 00:19:54.700
Here's to both Vincents

346
00:19:54.600 --> 00:19:57.300
In a Japanese mode
like the painting!

347
00:19:57.200 --> 00:20:17.300
&nbsp

348
00:20:16.500 --> 00:20:18.100
Rene is so talented

349
00:20:18.000 --> 00:20:20.900
I know

350
00:20:20.800 --> 00:20:25.100
&nbsp

351
00:20:24.900 --> 00:20:28.100
That awful sun. the
green sky..

352
00:20:28.000 --> 00:20:30.400
Who are those creeps?

353
00:20:30.300 --> 00:20:30.600
&nbsp

354
00:20:30.600 --> 00:20:33.100
-They help sell you!
-I doubt it

355
00:20:33.000 --> 00:20:37.000
Remove my paintings from Tanguy's
It's a pigsty. They'll rot!

356
00:20:36.800 --> 00:20:39.400
-Where do I put them?
-Under your bed!

357
00:20:39.300 --> 00:20:42.500
-Or can't the maid sweep?
-Jo sweeps!

358
00:20:42.400 --> 00:20:45.100
If Saint Jo does it...

359
00:20:45.000 --> 00:22:00.000
&nbsp

360
00:21:56.900 --> 00:21:58.200
Why are they in there?

361
00:21:58.200 --> 00:21:59.700
I don't know

362
00:21:59.600 --> 00:22:02.700
I'm a pain. right?

363
00:22:02.600 --> 00:22:07.200
&nbsp

364
00:22:07.000 --> 00:22:09.900
No. Vincent

365
00:22:09.800 --> 00:22:16.400
&nbsp

366
00:22:16.100 --> 00:22:18.900
Theo's not well

367
00:22:18.800 --> 00:22:20.100
&nbsp

368
00:22:20.000 --> 00:22:22.600
Dr. Gachet's not good
enough for him

369
00:22:22.500 --> 00:22:24.500
&nbsp

370
00:22:24.500 --> 00:22:28.100
How will it all end?

371
00:22:27.900 --> 00:22:32.800
You're the only one
I feel close to

372
00:22:32.600 --> 00:22:59.300
&nbsp

373
00:22:58.200 --> 00:23:00.600
One must be selfish

374
00:23:00.500 --> 00:23:01.700
&nbsp

375
00:23:01.700 --> 00:23:04.900
Theo doesn't know how to be

376
00:23:04.800 --> 00:23:08.800
&nbsp

377
00:23:08.600 --> 00:23:12.600
That's what I am. selfish

378
00:23:12.400 --> 00:23:32.100
&nbsp

379
00:23:31.300 --> 00:23:35.400
I can't whistle

380
00:23:35.300 --> 00:23:38.500
Pity you made two holes
in the painting

381
00:23:38.300 --> 00:23:44.400
&nbsp

382
00:23:44.200 --> 00:23:49.400
You touched my wife?
And you're so out of touch

383
00:23:49.200 --> 00:23:49.500
&nbsp

384
00:23:49.500 --> 00:23:52.500
You don't paint ones like her
You like sluts!

385
00:23:52.300 --> 00:23:54.600
And you?

386
00:23:54.500 --> 00:24:01.800
&nbsp

387
00:24:01.600 --> 00:24:05.800
See you soon. We'll settle
in all..

388
00:24:05.600 --> 00:24:08.500
Thanks for coming

389
00:24:08.400 --> 00:24:10.700
&nbsp

390
00:24:10.600 --> 00:24:14.200
You're awful
You quarrel with everyone

391
00:24:14.000 --> 00:24:14.200
&nbsp

392
00:24:14.200 --> 00:24:16.400
Even Gachet.
You fought with him

393
00:24:16.300 --> 00:24:18.800
You're rude to Aurier

394
00:24:18.700 --> 00:24:20.200
&nbsp

395
00:24:20.200 --> 00:24:26.300
You know
ciritics like Aurier sell art

396
00:24:26.000 --> 00:24:28.600
Buyers are
more influenced by..

397
00:24:28.500 --> 00:24:30.600
what they read than
what they see

398
00:24:30.500 --> 00:24:31.400
You know it

399
00:24:31.400 --> 00:24:36.200
Yes. they read a alot
of gibberish about beauty

400
00:24:36.000 --> 00:24:38.900
and have their minds
all set

401
00:24:38.800 --> 00:24:43.400
Critics praise good and bad
so buters lap it all up

402
00:24:43.200 --> 00:24:45.300
It's called eclecticism

403
00:24:45.200 --> 00:24:46.800
Shit!

404
00:24:46.700 --> 00:24:50.600
&nbsp

405
00:24:50.500 --> 00:24:53.000
You got it made!

406
00:24:52.900 --> 00:24:59.100
&nbsp

407
00:24:58.800 --> 00:25:02.100
And you neglect
the best painter of our time!

408
00:25:02.000 --> 00:25:03.100
You're the best?

409
00:25:03.100 --> 00:25:06.500
Yes. I am. You sleep on my
work. It's under your bed

410
00:25:06.300 --> 00:25:08.500
-Where do I put it?
-Show it!

411
00:25:08.400 --> 00:25:10.400
You wrote me not to!

412
00:25:10.300 --> 00:25:13.500
All my work!
You got it for nothing!

413
00:25:13.400 --> 00:25:17.500
How can you say that?
You're awful

414
00:25:17.300 --> 00:25:19.400
One day
I'll stop supporting you

415
00:25:19.400 --> 00:25:25.700
You're just a dealer who
exploits artists. a slave driver

416
00:25:25.400 --> 00:25:28.200
You buy cheap. anyway
From me you get..

417
00:25:28.100 --> 00:25:33.500
20 works a month for the price
of one second-rate impressionist

418
00:25:33.300 --> 00:25:35.200
You're vile

419
00:25:35.100 --> 00:25:37.100
You must be revolted
by your own words!

420
00:25:37.000 --> 00:25:39.400
You've ruined our
relationship

421
00:25:39.300 --> 00:25:42.600
Good. I'm not scared

422
00:25:42.500 --> 00:25:46.200
I'll be better off
I've been sponging

423
00:25:46.000 --> 00:25:49.800
All those paintings are yours
Forever!

424
00:25:49.700 --> 00:25:54.100
Fine words! "Forever!" If I
died. who'd get my paintings?

425
00:25:53.900 --> 00:25:58.400
Who? You might destroy them
like Mother did at home!

426
00:25:58.200 --> 00:26:01.800
No one in the family believe
in me. No one!

427
00:26:01.700 --> 00:26:04.800
"Get rid of these" She said

428
00:26:04.700 --> 00:26:08.300
She didn't Who told you that?

429
00:26:08.100 --> 00:26:09.000
&nbsp

430
00:26:09.000 --> 00:26:11.700
I happen to know it

431
00:26:11.600 --> 00:26:13.900
&nbsp

432
00:26:13.800 --> 00:26:17.300
I was a coward to accept your
money. I became a drone

433
00:26:17.100 --> 00:26:21.200
What's worse. I feel I'm
being kept

434
00:26:21.100 --> 00:26:25.500
The shame! better
to be a dock-worker

435
00:26:25.300 --> 00:26:29.400
One can't work and paint
Those who tried stopped painting

436
00:26:29.200 --> 00:26:33.300
Gauguin painted for years
as a stockbroker

437
00:26:33.100 --> 00:26:33.500
&nbsp

438
00:26:33.500 --> 00:26:35.100
You smothered me

439
00:26:35.100 --> 00:26:40.200
I'd have worked harder. better
I've done nothing great

440
00:26:40.000 --> 00:26:46.900
&nbsp

441
00:26:46.600 --> 00:26:49.600
And life's too sad

442
00:26:49.500 --> 00:26:52.100
I'm at the end of my tether

443
00:26:52.000 --> 00:26:54.900
Haven't you noticed?

444
00:26:54.700 --> 00:26:57.000
My painting is shit

445
00:26:56.900 --> 00:26:57.100
&nbsp

446
00:26:57.100 --> 00:27:00.700
Seen my portrait
of Marguerite Gachet? Crap!

447
00:27:00.600 --> 00:27:03.400
It's a transition
Don't exaggerate

448
00:27:03.300 --> 00:27:07.000
You've been there 2 months
You can't always be on top

449
00:27:06.800 --> 00:27:09.900
On top?
You've never liked what I do

450
00:27:09.800 --> 00:27:15.500
A kind word here and there
but I know your taste

451
00:27:15.300 --> 00:27:19.600
You've never spoken
this way. Never

452
00:27:19.400 --> 00:27:23.200
I'm sick
I can't keep this up for long

453
00:27:23.000 --> 00:27:25.700
No. not for long

454
00:27:25.600 --> 00:27:26.800
&nbsp

455
00:27:26.800 --> 00:27:28.400
I've never
had pains like this

456
00:27:28.300 --> 00:27:30.800
Seen a doctor?

457
00:27:30.700 --> 00:27:33.800
He didnt' understand me

458
00:27:33.700 --> 00:27:35.000
You in pain now?

459
00:27:34.900 --> 00:27:38.800
You are harder to bear
We've had our problems

460
00:27:38.700 --> 00:27:41.700
but your present mood..

461
00:27:41.600 --> 00:27:42.600
What?

462
00:27:42.500 --> 00:27:45.000
You're healthy and close
to success!

463
00:27:44.900 --> 00:27:46.900
But my painting's worse!

464
00:27:46.800 --> 00:27:50.500
Aurier's piece has made you
And your fits

465
00:27:50.400 --> 00:27:51.700
They're over!

466
00:27:51.600 --> 00:27:55.900
Listen. Theo

467
00:27:55.800 --> 00:27:57.000
There are no fits

468
00:27:56.900 --> 00:28:00.500
I never had any

469
00:28:00.400 --> 00:28:05.900
There were tricks. like
a squid spurts ink to hide

470
00:28:05.600 --> 00:28:11.400
I'm telling you. it won't be a fit
but a calm decision. if I can...

471
00:28:11.200 --> 00:28:16.800
to put an end to what's
unbearable for me and all of us

472
00:28:16.600 --> 00:28:18.200
&nbsp

473
00:28:18.100 --> 00:28:23.600
I'm not as selfish as you say
I do think of others

474
00:28:23.400 --> 00:28:24.000
&nbsp

475
00:28:24.000 --> 00:28:29.300
I didn't come to settle a
score. just to say hello

476
00:28:29.100 --> 00:28:34.400
&nbsp

477
00:28:34.100 --> 00:28:36.500
Lautrec's always late

478
00:28:36.400 --> 00:28:38.100
&nbsp

479
00:28:38.100 --> 00:28:40.700
Vincent? Come eat

480
00:28:40.600 --> 00:28:47.300
&nbsp

481
00:28:47.000 --> 00:28:52.600
Really!

482
00:28:52.400 --> 00:28:58.800
&nbsp

483
00:28:58.500 --> 00:28:59.900
Hare?

484
00:28:59.800 --> 00:29:00.900
&nbsp

485
00:29:00.900 --> 00:29:04.100
Will you stay in Auvers?

486
00:29:04.000 --> 00:29:05.400
I'll leave

487
00:29:05.300 --> 00:29:06.800
Where? With no money?

488
00:29:06.800 --> 00:29:09.000
Who do we paint for?

489
00:29:08.900 --> 00:29:12.000
Rich collectors
connoisseurs...

490
00:29:11.800 --> 00:29:15.500
assoholes...the worst
We paint for them

491
00:29:15.400 --> 00:29:17.200
Dump all my stuff

492
00:29:17.100 --> 00:29:19.600
You've got over 200
that's 20.000 francs

493
00:29:19.500 --> 00:29:23.900
I can't unload all that
by an unknown artist

494
00:29:23.700 --> 00:29:25.500
Who's to blame?

495
00:29:25.500 --> 00:29:26.900
Make up your mind

496
00:29:26.800 --> 00:29:28.200
I'm off

497
00:29:28.200 --> 00:29:35.800
&nbsp

498
00:29:35.400 --> 00:29:37.200
Hear of Schubert?

499
00:29:37.200 --> 00:29:38.600
&nbsp

500
00:29:38.500 --> 00:29:39.900
What about him?

501
00:29:39.900 --> 00:29:43.700
Yes. Schubert

502
00:29:43.500 --> 00:29:43.700
&nbsp

503
00:29:43.700 --> 00:29:45.000
Didn't you know?

504
00:29:44.900 --> 00:29:46.700
All his friends dumped him..

505
00:29:46.700 --> 00:29:48.600
to avoid catching 
his disease

506
00:29:48.500 --> 00:29:49.700
What's the connection?

507
00:29:49.600 --> 00:29:51.800
Don't you see?

508
00:29:51.800 --> 00:29:54.900
&nbsp

509
00:29:54.700 --> 00:29:58.200
You notice too late
you have no friends..

510
00:29:58.100 --> 00:30:01.500
if you can still
notice things..

511
00:30:01.400 --> 00:30:01.600
&nbsp

512
00:30:01.500 --> 00:30:03.700
Just as well

513
00:30:03.700 --> 00:30:04.200
&nbsp

514
00:30:04.100 --> 00:30:05.100
You're crazy!

515
00:30:05.100 --> 00:30:06.400
&nbsp

516
00:30:06.300 --> 00:30:07.600
Stop that!

517
00:30:07.600 --> 00:30:15.600
&nbsp

518
00:30:15.300 --> 00:30:18.400
It's weakness. Vincent

519
00:30:18.200 --> 00:30:18.500
&nbsp

520
00:30:18.500 --> 00:30:21.600
When there's no more hay
horses fight

521
00:30:21.500 --> 00:30:43.100
&nbsp

522
00:30:42.200 --> 00:30:45.000
I can't stand them

523
00:30:44.900 --> 00:30:49.300
Find some buyers. I can't
stand them. Get rid of them!

524
00:30:49.100 --> 00:30:49.800
&nbsp

525
00:30:49.800 --> 00:30:53.600
Look. I didn't do that!

526
00:30:53.400 --> 00:30:54.500
&nbsp

527
00:30:54.500 --> 00:30:58.100
Did I paint that eye?

528
00:30:58.000 --> 00:31:03.100
Those shaded greys.
the contour of the eyes..

529
00:31:02.900 --> 00:31:05.400
I did that?

530
00:31:05.300 --> 00:31:07.300
Impossible

531
00:31:07.200 --> 00:31:12.000
I paint receding chins
in banal complementary colors

532
00:31:11.800 --> 00:31:15.300
Dump them or sell them
Selling is dumping for money!

533
00:31:15.100 --> 00:31:18.100
I can't

534
00:31:18.000 --> 00:31:19.600
You can't?

535
00:31:19.500 --> 00:31:22.900
&nbsp

536
00:31:22.800 --> 00:31:25.200
NO one wants them. right?

537
00:31:25.100 --> 00:31:35.500
&nbsp

538
00:31:35.100 --> 00:31:36.400
What?

539
00:31:36.300 --> 00:31:37.400
Nothing. Vincent

540
00:31:37.400 --> 00:31:39.300
"Nothing. Vincent"

541
00:31:39.200 --> 00:31:44.700
&nbsp

542
00:31:44.500 --> 00:31:48.400
I bet if I throw
them out the window..

543
00:31:48.200 --> 00:31:53.400
..they'll be there tomorrow
No one'll touch them

544
00:31:53.200 --> 00:31:53.700
&nbsp

545
00:31:53.700 --> 00:31:56.300
Even garbage men and bums

546
00:31:56.200 --> 00:32:09.200
&nbsp

547
00:32:08.700 --> 00:32:12.000
Here. Mr. Van Gogh. your
onion soup

548
00:32:11.800 --> 00:32:16.800
&nbsp

549
00:32:16.600 --> 00:32:18.300
You well. Vincent?

550
00:32:18.300 --> 00:32:20.700
&nbsp

551
00:32:20.600 --> 00:32:22.100
What's up?

552
00:32:22.000 --> 00:32:23.600
I'm having my soup

553
00:32:23.500 --> 00:32:25.200
Glad you're back in Paris

554
00:32:25.200 --> 00:32:32.800
&nbsp

555
00:32:32.500 --> 00:32:34.000
What're you up to?

556
00:32:33.900 --> 00:32:35.800
Having my soup

557
00:32:35.700 --> 00:32:52.100
&nbsp

558
00:32:51.500 --> 00:32:54.600
Here's big Suzanne V

559
00:32:54.400 --> 00:32:54.600
&nbsp

560
00:32:54.600 --> 00:32:56.000
Back in Paris?

561
00:32:56.000 --> 00:32:56.200
&nbsp

562
00:32:56.200 --> 00:32:59.100
I just want to eat my soup

563
00:32:58.900 --> 00:33:01.100
You know I paint now

564
00:33:01.100 --> 00:33:04.600
Dear Suzanne..Everyone
paints now. even women

565
00:33:04.400 --> 00:33:05.500
&nbsp

566
00:33:05.500 --> 00:33:07.700
How would he live without you?

567
00:33:07.600 --> 00:33:09.700
Maybe he'd die!

568
00:33:09.600 --> 00:33:11.900
He'd die!

569
00:33:11.800 --> 00:33:14.200
He'd get a job like
everyone else

570
00:33:14.100 --> 00:33:17.300
I've known men as talented
as he...

571
00:33:17.200 --> 00:33:19.800
...who wanted to live off
their art

572
00:33:19.700 --> 00:33:23.400
They took jobs
Like everyone. Real jobs

573
00:33:23.200 --> 00:33:24.800
&nbsp

574
00:33:24.800 --> 00:33:27.300
Being an artist is a luxury

575
00:33:27.200 --> 00:33:30.100
You must be able to afford it

576
00:33:29.900 --> 00:33:30.500
&nbsp

577
00:33:30.500 --> 00:33:34.300
I'm sick of hearing of their
sufferings

578
00:33:34.200 --> 00:33:34.400
&nbsp

579
00:33:34.400 --> 00:33:37.300
The poor really suffer

580
00:33:37.100 --> 00:33:37.800
&nbsp

581
00:33:37.800 --> 00:33:41.200
They have no work. no food

582
00:33:41.100 --> 00:33:43.300
Vincent is your showgirl!

583
00:33:43.200 --> 00:33:46.300
-You can't afford him!
-I've managed

584
00:33:46.200 --> 00:33:49.800
It has to change

585
00:33:49.600 --> 00:33:50.400
&nbsp

586
00:33:50.400 --> 00:33:56.200
You have a family now
Not just yours. Ours!

587
00:33:55.900 --> 00:33:57.400
&nbsp

588
00:33:57.400 --> 00:34:01.900
You'll support that wreck all
your life?

589
00:34:01.700 --> 00:34:02.500
&nbsp

590
00:34:02.500 --> 00:34:04.400
Shut up!

591
00:34:04.300 --> 00:34:05.200
Stop that!

592
00:34:05.200 --> 00:34:06.800
-You're vulgar. Johanna
-Yes. I am!

593
00:34:06.700 --> 00:34:08.600
Stop that!

594
00:34:08.500 --> 00:34:18.000
&nbsp

595
00:34:17.600 --> 00:34:20.300
Coming!

596
00:34:20.200 --> 00:34:22.400
&nbsp

597
00:34:22.300 --> 00:34:23.900
What's happened?

598
00:34:23.900 --> 00:34:28.000
He wasn't on the train
He's not back. Where is he?

599
00:34:27.800 --> 00:34:28.800
You must have crossed him...

600
00:34:28.800 --> 00:34:33.000
He's not back. I'm sure

601
00:34:32.800 --> 00:34:33.500
&nbsp

602
00:34:33.500 --> 00:34:35.900
He can only be one place

603
00:34:35.800 --> 00:34:38.300
You know it. Take her there

604
00:34:38.200 --> 00:34:46.200
&nbsp

605
00:34:45.800 --> 00:34:46.900
A drink?

606
00:34:46.900 --> 00:34:49.000
No. Thanks

607
00:34:48.900 --> 00:34:51.200
&nbsp

608
00:34:51.100 --> 00:34:51.900
Have you eaten?

609
00:34:51.900 --> 00:34:53.700
I'm not hungry

610
00:34:53.600 --> 00:35:02.900
&nbsp

611
00:35:02.500 --> 00:35:03.900
Let's go

612
00:35:03.900 --> 00:35:04.600
&nbsp

613
00:35:04.500 --> 00:35:06.400
It'll be like
the good old days

614
00:35:06.400 --> 00:39:08.500
&nbsp

615
00:38:58.700 --> 00:39:00.800
You're heavy!

616
00:39:00.700 --> 00:39:02.800
&nbsp

617
00:39:02.700 --> 00:39:04.300
You look content

618
00:39:04.200 --> 00:39:04.500
&nbsp

619
00:39:04.600 --> 00:39:08.600
You're new here
I don't know you

620
00:39:08.400 --> 00:39:12.300
&nbsp

621
00:39:12.200 --> 00:39:14.900
You're married. right?
Brought your wife?

622
00:39:14.800 --> 00:39:17.200
She was too tired

623
00:39:17.100 --> 00:39:18.200
&nbsp

624
00:39:18.100 --> 00:39:19.500
She had her baby?

625
00:39:19.500 --> 00:39:22.500
3 months ago. He's big

626
00:39:22.300 --> 00:39:24.400
Should've brought her.

627
00:39:24.300 --> 00:39:26.200
She's teasing

628
00:39:26.200 --> 00:39:26.800
&nbsp

629
00:39:26.700 --> 00:39:30.100
She'd love it here!

630
00:39:30.000 --> 00:39:31.600
Your name?

631
00:39:31.500 --> 00:39:31.800
&nbsp

632
00:39:31.800 --> 00:39:32.600
Cathy

633
00:39:32.600 --> 00:39:36.900
Pretty name. You have nice
rings. pretty hands

634
00:39:36.700 --> 00:40:13.800
&nbsp

635
00:40:12.300 --> 00:40:14.300
-How are things. Suzanne?
-All right

636
00:40:14.200 --> 00:40:17.600
How's Puvis de Chavanne' Kid?

637
00:40:17.500 --> 00:40:17.900
&nbsp

638
00:40:17.900 --> 00:40:19.100
He's 7 now

639
00:40:19.000 --> 00:40:20.600
Time flies

640
00:40:20.600 --> 00:40:24.600
&nbsp

641
00:40:24.400 --> 00:40:26.800
Did you wipe out Henri?

642
00:40:26.700 --> 00:40:30.200
He always naps after it.

643
00:40:30.100 --> 00:41:08.700
&nbsp

644
00:41:07.100 --> 00:41:08.900
Not wearing socks?

645
00:41:08.800 --> 00:41:10.400
I left in a hurry

646
00:41:10.400 --> 00:41:12.600
-Your wife kicked you out?
-Sort of..

647
00:41:12.500 --> 00:41:16.400
&nbsp

648
00:41:16.200 --> 00:41:19.000
Play something more...more..

649
00:41:18.900 --> 00:41:39.900
&nbsp

650
00:41:39.000 --> 00:41:40.300
I'm busy

651
00:41:40.300 --> 00:41:40.400
&nbsp

652
00:41:40.400 --> 00:41:41.800
I came to Paris just for that

653
00:41:41.700 --> 00:41:43.900
I always did you well...

654
00:41:43.800 --> 00:41:48.700
Don't touch me

655
00:41:48.500 --> 00:41:49.200
&nbsp

656
00:41:49.200 --> 00:41:51.300
You crazy?

657
00:41:51.200 --> 00:41:51.700
&nbsp

658
00:41:51.700 --> 00:41:54.900
I looked for you in Auvers.
left you a note

659
00:41:54.800 --> 00:41:57.900
&nbsp

660
00:41:57.800 --> 00:41:58.700
Can we meet?

661
00:41:58.600 --> 00:42:00.100
Hands off!

662
00:42:00.100 --> 00:42:01.600
Tomrrow...the day after..

663
00:42:01.500 --> 00:42:03.900
Sure...You can't be
bothered..

664
00:42:03.800 --> 00:42:05.200
Let go...

665
00:42:05.100 --> 00:42:06.100
&nbsp

666
00:42:06.100 --> 00:42:07.600
Hands off!

667
00:42:07.500 --> 00:42:08.800
&nbsp

668
00:42:08.800 --> 00:42:12.500
Your sweetness is phony

669
00:42:12.300 --> 00:42:13.000
&nbsp

670
00:42:13.000 --> 00:42:15.800
Asshole! Go home!

671
00:42:15.700 --> 00:42:17.200
Who needs you!

672
00:42:17.100 --> 00:42:18.300
&nbsp

673
00:42:18.300 --> 00:42:21.200
The whore with the heart of
gold!

674
00:42:21.100 --> 00:42:24.600
You're so romantic
you're a goner!

675
00:42:24.400 --> 00:43:04.500
&nbsp

676
00:43:02.900 --> 00:43:04.000
She's shy

677
00:43:04.000 --> 00:43:57.000
&nbsp

678
00:43:54.800 --> 00:43:56.200
Sing "Red Hill"

679
00:43:56.100 --> 00:43:58.100
&nbsp

680
00:43:58.100 --> 00:43:59.900
"It's called Red Hill..

681
00:43:59.800 --> 00:44:05.900
"...and here's why. All who fought here
were doomed to die

682
00:44:05.600 --> 00:44:09.200
"Now it's a vineyard
like so many others...

683
00:44:09.100 --> 00:44:14.100
"But when you drink its wine. you
drink the blood of your brothers

684
00:44:13.900 --> 00:44:17.400
"There were no pretty maids
on that hill...

685
00:44:17.300 --> 00:44:19.900
"...no swains. no laughter
and mirth

686
00:44:19.700 --> 00:44:25.100
"It's far from Montmartre and
Paris. the hub of the earth

687
00:44:24.900 --> 00:44:29.300
"That hill is soaked in the
blood...

688
00:44:29.100 --> 00:44:31.800
"...of farmers and workers
who answered a call

689
00:44:31.700 --> 00:44:37.100
"Those who start wars
never die of them...

690
00:44:36.900 --> 00:44:40.300
"...only the innocent fall

691
00:44:40.200 --> 00:44:41.600
"Red Hill..

692
00:44:41.500 --> 00:44:43.200
"...is its name...

693
00:44:43.200 --> 00:44:48.700
"...and here's why. All who fought here
were doomed to die

694
00:44:48.400 --> 00:44:53.100
"Now it's a vineyard
like so many others...

695
00:44:52.900 --> 00:45:04.300
"But when you drink its wine. you
drink the blood of your brothers

696
00:45:03.900 --> 00:45:05.000
&nbsp

697
00:45:04.900 --> 00:45:08.000
May I

698
00:45:07.900 --> 00:45:10.000
Here. taste

699
00:45:09.900 --> 00:45:11.900
&nbsp

700
00:45:11.800 --> 00:45:12.700
It's good

701
00:45:12.700 --> 00:45:14.800
Drink..

702
00:45:14.700 --> 00:45:18.400
&nbsp

703
00:45:18.300 --> 00:45:22.100
More...

704
00:45:21.900 --> 00:45:28.000
&nbsp

705
00:45:27.800 --> 00:45:29.300
You love me?

706
00:45:29.200 --> 00:45:30.900
&nbsp

707
00:45:30.800 --> 00:45:32.200
Say it

708
00:45:32.200 --> 00:46:46.000
&nbsp

709
00:46:43.000 --> 00:46:46.800
Come. brother.
Time to parade! Look sharp!

710
00:46:46.600 --> 00:50:51.800
&nbsp

711
00:50:41.900 --> 00:50:45.700
-Will you buy my paintings?
-I did...Which ones?

712
00:50:45.500 --> 00:50:47.800
Those I paint!

713
00:50:47.700 --> 00:50:47.900
&nbsp

714
00:50:47.900 --> 00:50:52.600
You're known as a model!
No one wants your paintings!

715
00:50:52.400 --> 00:50:56.200
Bastard! Now you're like all
the dealers

716
00:50:56.100 --> 00:50:57.000
&nbsp

717
00:50:56.900 --> 00:51:00.400
I need sleep before
I open my gallery

718
00:51:00.300 --> 00:51:00.500
&nbsp

719
00:51:00.500 --> 00:51:03.000
I'll go snooze with my
old lady

720
00:51:02.900 --> 00:51:15.200
&nbsp

721
00:51:14.700 --> 00:51:16.800
Third class is narrow

722
00:51:16.700 --> 00:51:20.500
Sure. the poor have
smaller asses

723
00:51:20.300 --> 00:51:50.300
&nbsp

724
00:51:49.100 --> 00:51:50.800
This is living

725
00:51:50.800 --> 00:52:04.400
&nbsp

726
00:52:03.800 --> 00:52:05.000
Tickets please

727
00:52:05.000 --> 00:52:08.900
&nbsp

728
00:52:08.700 --> 00:52:12.500
Kiss again. it's the
milk-train! Have a nice trip!

729
00:52:12.300 --> 00:52:34.800
&nbsp

730
00:52:33.900 --> 00:52:35.300
What's wrong?

731
00:52:35.300 --> 00:52:52.100
&nbsp

732
00:52:51.400 --> 00:52:53.800
I so wish you loved me...

733
00:52:53.700 --> 00:53:01.700
&nbsp

734
00:53:01.400 --> 00:53:03.600
I know you don't

735
00:53:03.500 --> 00:53:04.300
&nbsp

736
00:53:04.300 --> 00:53:05.800
Doesn't matter

737
00:53:05.700 --> 00:53:12.300
&nbsp

738
00:53:12.000 --> 00:53:13.700
What have I done?

739
00:53:13.700 --> 00:53:16.200
&nbsp

740
00:53:16.100 --> 00:53:18.500
Answer when I ask you!

741
00:53:18.400 --> 00:53:24.000
&nbsp

742
00:53:23.700 --> 00:53:27.100
You can't take paintings
to the grave!

743
00:53:27.000 --> 00:53:27.600
&nbsp

744
00:53:27.600 --> 00:53:30.800
Painting! It's a disease

745
00:53:30.600 --> 00:53:30.800
&nbsp

746
00:53:30.800 --> 00:53:32.900
You're sick. you hear!

747
00:53:32.800 --> 00:53:35.900
You grovel in your shit!
Your shitty paintings!

748
00:53:35.800 --> 00:53:35.900
&nbsp

749
00:53:36.000 --> 00:53:37.900
&nbsp
From your sick mind!

750
00:53:37.800 --> 00:53:38.600
&nbsp

751
00:53:38.600 --> 00:53:40.100
Let go of me!

752
00:53:40.000 --> 00:53:41.700
You're not normal!

753
00:53:41.700 --> 00:53:41.900
&nbsp

754
00:53:41.900 --> 00:53:43.800
You're insane! Stay there!

755
00:53:43.700 --> 00:53:44.000
&nbsp

756
00:53:44.000 --> 00:53:45.400
Sit down!

757
00:53:45.300 --> 00:54:12.900
&nbsp

758
00:54:11.800 --> 00:54:13.000
Here

759
00:54:12.900 --> 00:54:15.200
&nbsp

760
00:54:15.200 --> 00:54:18.200
You're alone? Where's my
daugher?

761
00:54:18.000 --> 00:54:20.700
-Your ugly face!
-She vanished yesterday

762
00:54:20.600 --> 00:54:31.600
&nbsp

763
00:54:31.200 --> 00:54:32.800
-What happened?
-Nothing

764
00:54:32.700 --> 00:54:34.400
-What did he do to you?
-Nothing

765
00:54:34.300 --> 00:54:34.600
&nbsp

766
00:54:34.600 --> 00:54:36.300
Answer

767
00:54:36.300 --> 00:54:36.600
&nbsp

768
00:54:36.500 --> 00:54:38.200
Are you ill?

769
00:54:38.200 --> 00:54:52.100
&nbsp

770
00:54:51.500 --> 00:54:55.000
There's no need to destroy
to create!

771
00:54:54.900 --> 00:54:55.100
&nbsp

772
00:54:55.100 --> 00:54:56.300
You sow despair

773
00:54:56.200 --> 00:54:56.400
&nbsp

774
00:54:56.400 --> 00:54:58.800
A great artist
but a loathsome man

775
00:54:58.700 --> 00:54:58.800
&nbsp

776
00:54:58.800 --> 00:55:02.700
You're twice her age!
Aren't you ashamed?

777
00:55:02.500 --> 00:55:02.700
&nbsp

778
00:55:02.700 --> 00:55:06.800
I've known many painters
They weren't like you

779
00:55:06.700 --> 00:55:10.400
You're vulgar
It's in everything you do

780
00:55:10.200 --> 00:55:19.700
&nbsp

781
00:55:19.300 --> 00:55:21.600
You don't love me
You don't care

782
00:55:21.500 --> 00:55:21.700
&nbsp

783
00:55:21.700 --> 00:55:24.300
If you knew how I love you...

784
00:55:24.200 --> 00:55:30.900
&nbsp

785
00:55:30.700 --> 00:55:32.500
You forgot your package

786
00:55:32.400 --> 00:56:06.600
&nbsp

787
00:56:05.200 --> 00:56:09.600
Go out onto the platform
The young lady's unwell

788
00:56:09.400 --> 00:56:27.700
&nbsp

789
00:56:27.000 --> 00:56:28.800
-Get help!
-A doctor?

790
00:56:28.700 --> 00:56:31.700
I'm a doctor. idiot!
A carriage

791
00:56:31.600 --> 00:56:40.100
&nbsp

792
00:56:39.700 --> 00:56:43.700
Take her feet...
Climb up and lift her..

793
00:56:43.600 --> 00:56:54.600
&nbsp

794
00:56:54.100 --> 00:56:56.600
-What are you eating?
-A bun

795
00:56:56.500 --> 00:56:57.500
&nbsp

796
00:56:57.500 --> 00:56:59.000
Can I have some?

797
00:56:58.900 --> 00:57:08.500
&nbsp

798
00:57:08.100 --> 00:57:09.500
Good. huh?

799
00:57:09.500 --> 00:57:12.900
&nbsp

800
00:57:12.700 --> 00:57:15.100
Here. take that

801
00:57:15.000 --> 00:57:23.100
&nbsp

802
00:57:22.800 --> 00:57:23.300
Come on..

803
00:57:23.300 --> 00:57:27.600
&nbsp

804
00:57:27.400 --> 00:57:29.900
-Where you off to?
-To watch him paint

805
00:57:29.800 --> 00:57:30.100
&nbsp

806
00:57:30.100 --> 00:57:32.800
Matching loonies!
Why's that here?

807
00:57:32.700 --> 00:57:32.900
&nbsp

808
00:57:32.900 --> 00:57:36.200
Do other hotels let'em
paint...

809
00:57:36.100 --> 00:57:39.500
...indoors?
Soon it'll be in the bar!

810
00:57:39.300 --> 00:57:42.700
It won't be a bar
but a paint store!

811
00:57:42.600 --> 00:58:03.400
&nbsp

812
00:58:02.500 --> 00:58:04.700
You didn't do my ear

813
00:58:04.600 --> 00:58:18.000
&nbsp

814
00:58:17.500 --> 00:58:18.900
Move over

815
00:58:18.800 --> 00:58:29.100
&nbsp

816
00:58:28.700 --> 00:58:30.600
Some day
we'll do this for free

817
00:58:30.500 --> 00:58:30.700
&nbsp

818
00:58:30.700 --> 00:58:31.600
Normally...

819
00:58:31.600 --> 00:58:32.900
Right. it'll be nice

820
00:58:32.800 --> 00:58:38.800
&nbsp

821
00:58:38.600 --> 00:58:39.900
Let's start now

822
00:58:39.900 --> 00:58:40.100
&nbsp

823
00:58:40.000 --> 00:58:41.100
What?

824
00:58:41.100 --> 00:58:42.500
For free

825
00:58:42.400 --> 00:58:43.800
Really?

826
00:58:43.800 --> 00:58:45.300
&nbsp

827
00:58:45.200 --> 00:58:46.700
That send you?

828
00:58:46.700 --> 00:58:47.500
What?

829
00:58:47.400 --> 00:58:49.600
When I kiss your neck

830
00:58:49.500 --> 00:58:53.100
Well it does me. So do it.

831
00:58:53.000 --> 00:58:59.100
&nbsp

832
00:58:58.800 --> 00:59:01.300
Are you eating me?

833
00:59:01.200 --> 00:59:14.700
&nbsp

834
00:59:14.200 --> 00:59:16.800
Where's La Mouche?

835
00:59:16.700 --> 00:59:18.900
In Paris

836
00:59:18.800 --> 00:59:20.700
Hurry. I'm bushed

837
00:59:20.600 --> 01:01:06.800
&nbsp

838
01:01:02.500 --> 01:01:04.000
It'll be all right

839
01:01:04.000 --> 01:01:22.500
&nbsp

840
01:01:21.700 --> 01:01:23.600
Don't you want any?

841
01:01:23.500 --> 01:01:24.700
She doesn't

842
01:01:24.700 --> 01:01:26.500
Why not? What's wrong?

843
01:01:26.400 --> 01:01:28.800
Glass of wine?

844
01:01:28.700 --> 01:01:30.200
&nbsp

845
01:01:30.100 --> 01:01:32.300
Who was that?

846
01:01:32.300 --> 01:01:34.900
Mr. Van Gogh.

847
01:01:34.800 --> 01:01:35.000
&nbsp

848
01:01:34.900 --> 01:01:37.500
Why isn't he eating with us?

849
01:01:37.400 --> 01:01:44.000
&nbsp

850
01:01:43.800 --> 01:01:46.700
Go look. See what he's up to

851
01:01:46.600 --> 01:01:51.300
&nbsp

852
01:01:51.100 --> 01:01:53.300
Coming?

853
01:01:53.200 --> 01:01:56.200
&nbsp

854
01:01:56.100 --> 01:01:58.100
Go see what's up

855
01:01:58.000 --> 01:02:08.200
&nbsp

856
01:02:07.800 --> 01:02:11.100
Wants none

857
01:02:10.900 --> 01:02:11.300
&nbsp

858
01:02:11.300 --> 01:02:12.800
Just like your sister

859
01:02:12.700 --> 01:02:13.000
&nbsp

860
01:02:13.000 --> 01:02:15.200
Mom. come quick!

861
01:02:15.100 --> 01:02:15.400
&nbsp

862
01:02:15.400 --> 01:02:16.700
What is it?

863
01:02:16.700 --> 01:02:29.000
&nbsp

864
01:02:28.500 --> 01:02:33.400
-Suicide's great for a hotel!
-Some hotel! Three rooms!

865
01:02:33.200 --> 01:02:38.400
&nbsp

866
01:02:38.200 --> 01:02:40.200
Is it a bullet?

867
01:02:40.100 --> 01:02:40.300
&nbsp

868
01:02:40.300 --> 01:02:42.000
Yes. it is

869
01:02:41.900 --> 01:02:44.800
&nbsp

870
01:02:44.700 --> 01:02:47.000
Does that hurt?

871
01:02:46.900 --> 01:02:59.600
&nbsp

872
01:02:59.100 --> 01:03:04.900
Help me turn him over

873
01:03:04.600 --> 01:03:05.800
Gently

874
01:03:05.800 --> 01:04:18.600
&nbsp

875
01:04:15.600 --> 01:04:17.000
You in pain? Want a shot?

876
01:04:17.000 --> 01:04:17.300
&nbsp

877
01:04:17.300 --> 01:04:19.100
No shots

878
01:04:19.000 --> 01:04:19.200
&nbsp

879
01:04:19.200 --> 01:04:20.200
They scare me

880
01:04:20.200 --> 01:04:22.100
&nbsp

881
01:04:22.000 --> 01:04:24.000
Shall we operate?

882
01:04:23.900 --> 01:04:30.500
&nbsp

883
01:04:30.200 --> 01:04:32.000
Well. doctor?

884
01:04:32.000 --> 01:04:32.200
&nbsp

885
01:04:32.100 --> 01:04:36.700
He needs hot compresses
And clean his bed

886
01:04:36.600 --> 01:04:36.800
&nbsp

887
01:04:36.800 --> 01:04:38.400
Very well. doctor

888
01:04:38.300 --> 01:04:43.000
&nbsp

889
01:04:42.800 --> 01:04:48.800
An overdose of barbiturates
is easier to deal with

890
01:04:48.600 --> 01:04:48.900
&nbsp

891
01:04:48.800 --> 01:04:53.000
When your daughter
said it was suicide...

892
01:04:52.900 --> 01:04:56.700
I brought my stomach pump

893
01:04:56.500 --> 01:05:38.100
&nbsp

894
01:05:36.400 --> 01:05:38.200
We'll look after you

895
01:05:38.200 --> 01:05:45.700
&nbsp

896
01:05:45.300 --> 01:05:46.400
Doctor. where were you?

897
01:05:46.400 --> 01:05:46.600
&nbsp

898
01:05:46.600 --> 01:05:48.600
-I was away. Where is he?
-Upstairs

899
01:05:48.500 --> 01:05:48.700
&nbsp

900
01:05:48.700 --> 01:05:50.600
-May I?
-Go ahead

901
01:05:50.500 --> 01:05:58.700
&nbsp

902
01:05:58.400 --> 01:06:01.200
-Sorry...
-The casualty's next door

903
01:06:01.100 --> 01:06:34.000
&nbsp

904
01:06:32.600 --> 01:06:34.600
You won't let me examine you?

905
01:06:34.600 --> 01:06:45.300
&nbsp

906
01:06:44.800 --> 01:06:47.600
Well. doctor?

907
01:06:47.500 --> 01:06:47.900
&nbsp

908
01:06:47.900 --> 01:06:51.200
He's breathing normally

909
01:06:51.100 --> 01:06:53.200
As if he wasn't hurt

910
01:06:53.100 --> 01:06:53.300
&nbsp

911
01:06:53.300 --> 01:06:56.400
I'll open the door

912
01:06:56.200 --> 01:07:03.000
&nbsp

913
01:07:02.800 --> 01:07:04.000
They're doing nothing?

914
01:07:03.900 --> 01:07:04.000
&nbsp

915
01:07:04.000 --> 01:07:05.700
Don't say that

916
01:07:05.700 --> 01:07:05.800
&nbsp

917
01:07:05.700 --> 01:07:07.400
But they aren't!

918
01:07:07.400 --> 01:07:21.500
&nbsp

919
01:07:20.900 --> 01:07:22.600
Little one...

920
01:07:22.500 --> 01:07:37.200
&nbsp

921
01:07:36.600 --> 01:07:38.500
Dear Theo...

922
01:07:38.500 --> 01:07:49.300
&nbsp

923
01:07:48.800 --> 01:07:53.400
You shouldn't have come...
till I'd croaked

924
01:07:53.200 --> 01:08:11.000
&nbsp

925
01:08:10.300 --> 01:08:12.300
Is that position all right?

926
01:08:12.200 --> 01:08:14.900
&nbsp

927
01:08:14.800 --> 01:08:15.200
He chose it. Leave him in it

928
01:08:15.200 --> 01:08:24.600
&nbsp

929
01:08:24.200 --> 01:08:26.200
No. don't...

930
01:08:26.100 --> 01:08:27.200
&nbsp

931
01:08:27.200 --> 01:08:28.700
It's good for him

932
01:08:28.600 --> 01:08:30.000
Isn't drinking bad for him?

933
01:08:30.000 --> 01:08:33.200
Don't give him a thing

934
01:08:33.100 --> 01:08:33.200
&nbsp

935
01:08:33.100 --> 01:08:37.700
They've readied a room for you
Get some rest. I'll watch him

936
01:08:37.600 --> 01:09:06.200
&nbsp

937
01:09:05.000 --> 01:09:06.900
How is he?

938
01:09:06.800 --> 01:09:08.000
&nbsp

939
01:09:08.000 --> 01:09:11.300
Get me a brandy

940
01:09:11.100 --> 01:09:14.000
&nbsp

941
01:09:13.900 --> 01:09:18.900
He must be moved to a hospital
in Paris. And operated on.

942
01:09:18.700 --> 01:09:19.700
&nbsp

943
01:09:19.700 --> 01:09:22.800
Never...He can't be moved

944
01:09:22.700 --> 01:09:23.100
&nbsp

945
01:09:23.000 --> 01:09:25.100
It'd kill him

946
01:09:25.100 --> 01:09:25.300
&nbsp

947
01:09:25.200 --> 01:09:29.200
But he'll die if he 
lingers here

948
01:09:29.100 --> 01:09:29.300
&nbsp

949
01:09:29.300 --> 01:09:32.600
We can't do nothing
and let him die

950
01:09:32.400 --> 01:09:33.300
&nbsp

951
01:09:33.300 --> 01:09:35.400
He'll die of nothing!

952
01:09:35.300 --> 01:09:36.400
&nbsp

953
01:09:36.400 --> 01:09:40.400
If he's still alive after 12 hours
his organs must be intact

954
01:09:40.200 --> 01:09:40.600
&nbsp

955
01:09:40.600 --> 01:09:46.400
Even a surgeon would damage his
organs extracting the bullet

956
01:09:46.200 --> 01:09:47.000
&nbsp

957
01:09:46.900 --> 01:09:51.100
The journey alone 
may kill him

958
01:09:51.000 --> 01:09:51.700
&nbsp

959
01:09:51.600 --> 01:09:54.700
I agree with my colleague...

960
01:09:54.600 --> 01:09:54.900
&nbsp

961
01:09:54.900 --> 01:09:57.500
I think it's hopeless

962
01:09:57.400 --> 01:10:52.000
&nbsp

963
01:10:49.800 --> 01:10:50.900
All right?

964
01:10:50.800 --> 01:10:56.400
&nbsp

965
01:10:56.200 --> 01:10:58.600
I'm hungry

966
01:10:58.500 --> 01:11:23.600
&nbsp

967
01:11:22.600 --> 01:11:24.000
It's all over

968
01:11:23.900 --> 01:13:01.900
&nbsp

969
01:12:57.900 --> 01:12:59.500
I'll settle up

970
01:12:59.500 --> 01:13:07.500
&nbsp

971
01:13:07.200 --> 01:13:12.000
Board and lodging for June is due.
And Dr. Masery's two visits

972
01:13:11.800 --> 01:13:13.200
&nbsp

973
01:13:13.100 --> 01:13:14.900
Did he give you any paintings?

974
01:13:14.800 --> 01:13:15.000
&nbsp

975
01:13:15.000 --> 01:13:15.700
Two

976
01:13:15.700 --> 01:13:15.900
&nbsp

977
01:13:15.900 --> 01:13:17.500
Keep them. They're yours

978
01:13:17.400 --> 01:13:23.200
&nbsp

979
01:13:23.000 --> 01:13:26.900
Run along.
Don't tell your sister

980
01:13:26.700 --> 01:13:29.600
&nbsp

981
01:13:29.500 --> 01:13:33.800
I'll return the paintings
he left with me

982
01:13:33.600 --> 01:13:37.000
My portrait and my daugher's

983
01:13:36.900 --> 01:13:40.100
We were just storing them...

984
01:13:40.000 --> 01:13:45.800
You must keep them. He'll become
known through your collection

985
01:13:45.500 --> 01:13:50.200
If you mean it...
I'm very touched.

986
01:13:50.000 --> 01:13:58.600
&nbsp

987
01:13:58.300 --> 01:14:02.100
Mr. Van Gogh. I've done the
death certificate

988
01:14:01.900 --> 01:14:18.900
&nbsp

989
01:14:18.200 --> 01:14:19.800
My foot!

990
01:14:19.800 --> 01:14:21.700
I didn't mean to!

991
01:14:21.600 --> 01:14:24.200
&nbsp

992
01:14:24.100 --> 01:14:26.000
My foot's crushed and
you laught!

993
01:14:25.900 --> 01:14:27.700
I'm not laughing

994
01:14:27.600 --> 01:14:27.700
&nbsp

995
01:14:27.700 --> 01:14:30.300
Doctor!

996
01:14:30.200 --> 01:14:31.600
&nbsp

997
01:14:31.600 --> 01:14:33.200
My foot!

998
01:14:33.100 --> 01:14:37.900
&nbsp

999
01:14:37.700 --> 01:14:39.300
I'll massage you

1000
01:14:39.300 --> 01:14:39.400
&nbsp

1001
01:14:39.400 --> 01:14:41.100
I have a healing hand

1002
01:14:41.000 --> 01:14:46.200
&nbsp

1003
01:14:46.000 --> 01:14:46.800
Better?

1004
01:14:46.700 --> 01:14:49.100
Feels good

1005
01:14:49.000 --> 01:14:49.700
&nbsp

1006
01:14:49.700 --> 01:14:51.200
So good...

1007
01:14:51.200 --> 01:14:54.700
&nbsp

1008
01:14:54.500 --> 01:14:56.800
I never let anyone touch
my feet

1009
01:14:56.700 --> 01:14:57.200
&nbsp

1010
01:14:57.200 --> 01:14:58.500
That's much better

1011
01:14:58.400 --> 01:14:58.500
&nbsp

1012
01:14:58.500 --> 01:14:59.400
I'll help you

1013
01:14:59.400 --> 01:15:02.700
&nbsp

1014
01:15:02.600 --> 01:15:04.000
It'll take months...

1015
01:15:03.900 --> 01:15:04.100
&nbsp

1016
01:15:04.100 --> 01:15:05.700
...to heal

1017
01:15:05.600 --> 01:16:00.300
&nbsp

1018
01:15:58.100 --> 01:16:02.100
Hi. You from here?

1019
01:16:02.000 --> 01:16:03.800
This the hanged man's house?

1020
01:16:03.700 --> 01:16:06.600
No. it's on Pylon Street
No one hanged himself there

1021
01:16:06.500 --> 01:16:08.800
&nbsp

1022
01:16:08.700 --> 01:16:10.800
First time
you've painted here?

1023
01:16:10.700 --> 01:16:14.100
No. I come often

1024
01:16:14.000 --> 01:16:17.000
It's like all the greats
are still here

1025
01:16:16.800 --> 01:16:19.400
Pissarro. Cezanne...

1026
01:16:19.300 --> 01:16:21.900
...Daumier. Millet...

1027
01:16:21.800 --> 01:16:25.000
Millet never came
Daumier lived in Valmondois

1028
01:16:24.900 --> 01:16:27.800
He painted a studio door here

1029
01:16:27.700 --> 01:16:31.100
The owner will show it to you

1030
01:16:30.900 --> 01:16:31.100
&nbsp

1031
01:16:31.100 --> 01:16:33.500
What's the motif?

1032
01:16:33.400 --> 01:16:33.700
&nbsp

1033
01:16:33.700 --> 01:16:36.500
Don Quixote...

1034
01:16:36.400 --> 01:16:37.000
&nbsp

1035
01:16:37.000 --> 01:16:38.700
Van Gogh liked it a lot

1036
01:16:38.600 --> 01:16:40.900
You knew Van Gogh?

1037
01:16:40.800 --> 01:16:42.400
&nbsp

1038
01:16:42.400 --> 01:16:45.900
Yes. He was my friend.

1039
01:16:46.305 --> 01:17:46.231
